Mél : christiangauvrit(a)orange.fr


*Langues dîtes "régionales" (Suite -- 2 à la gazette du 9 décembre)
*I am writing you with regard to the opinion about bilinguism. As a 
Catalan, I completely disagree with your correspondent (and you as I 
see). The French people should examine how was French imposed in all 
territory. Can anybody assure that it was adopted 'volontiers' by the 
population? In Catalunya, everybody speaks Spanish, and everybody is 
taught in Catalan in primary schools. The level of competence of the 
students in Spanish is the same (if not better) as in other territories 
of Spain. Where is the problem? Concerning costs, is you ask Catalans if 
they want to spend some more money to preserve their language, it is 
clear that their response is a very clear yes. Reducing the debate to an 
economic problem is a rather simplistic approach. Following the same 
argument, one language for all countries would be cheaper.
Would you agree to suppress the teaching of French in France and all 
countries speak in English (of Chinese)?
Contact : Enric ESTEVE
E-mail: Enric.esteve(a)irta.cat 
<http://webmail.acta-informatique.fr/src/compose.php?send_to=Enric.esteve%40irta.cat>


