                      <br>
                      <b>ISESS Symposium 2011<br>
                      </b>27 - 29 June 2011 - BRNO, Czech Republic<br>
                      The conference is organised by the Masaryk
                      University in cooperation with IFIP, the Ministry
                      of the Environment of the Czech Republic, the
                      European Commission and the European Environment
                      Agency.<br>
                      The conference will display the state-of-the-art
                      in the development and implementation
                      environmental information systems and eEnvironment
                      services, with a special focus on the following
                      topics:<br>
                      - eEnvironment and cross-border services in the
                      Digital Agenda for Europe (chair session Jiri
                      Hrebicek)<br>
                      - Environmental Information Systems and Services -
                      Infrastructures and Platforms (chair session Arne
                      Berre)<br>
                      - Semantics and Environment - (chair session
                      Gerald Schimak)<br>
                      - Distributed Environmental Modelling (chair
                      session David Swayne)<br>
                      - Information Tools for Global Environmental
                      Assessment (chair session Ivan Holoubek and
                      Ladislav Dusek)<br>
                      - Advanced Approaches to Catchment Hydrology
                      Simulation (chair session Ralf Denzer)<br>
                      <br>
                      The conference is a meeting place for experts on
                      leading edge technologies, and it aims to foster
                      the standardization and integration of
                      environmental data and information flows in world,
                      which are essential pre-requirements for managing
                      our natural resources in a framework of
                      sustainable development. The ISESS 2011 conference
                      is open to governmental institutions,
                      international and intergovernmental organisations,
                      environmental agencies and networks, scientists,
                      academicians, politicians, businesses, public
                      administration and decision makers in the field of
                      environmental information, experts from ICT
                      industry, specialists of theoretical and applied
                      informatics, consultants, students and the
                      concerned public.<br>
                      See: <a title="Ce lien vers un site externe
                        s'ouvrira dans une nouvelle fen&ecirc;tre "
                        href="http://www.isess2011.org/" target="_blank">http://www.isess2011.org/</a><br>
